hopobject.body: I enjoy travelling caltagmedsystems.de Everett was right, but he left out one significant thing. If the universe splits up into two pieces, and one of them causes you to die so you can't observe that branch of the universe, then the only one you're going to observe is the one in which you survived. The one in which the bomb didn't go off, in which the ocean wasn't too acidic, in which there was just the right mix of oxygen and carbon and nitrogen in the atmosphere, in which a mid-sized planet revolved at the exact right distance around Â medium-sized star.
